Alta Devices Raises $72 Million in Funding for Thin-Film Solar Technology

-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 
2011-03-10T01:12:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/alta-devices-raises-72-million-in-funding-for-thin-film-solar-technology.html
Alta Devices Inc. , a U.S. company
that is developing thin-film solar technology, raised $72
million from its Series C funding round.  Alberta Investment Management Corp. led other new investors
that include Good Energies Inc., Energy Technology Ventures, a
joint venture involving  General Electric Co. (GE) ,  ConocoPhillips (COP)  and  NRG Energy Inc. (NRG) , and  Constellation Energy Group Inc. (CEG) ,  Abigail
Johnson, a spokeswoman for Alta Devices, said in an e-mail.  The funding round included previous investors August
Capital, Kleiner Perkins Caufield & Byers, Crosslink Capital,
DAG Ventures, New Enterprise Associates, Presidio Ventures,
Technology Partners and  Dow Chemical Co. (DOW) , Alta Devices said in a
statement.  Santa Clara, California-based Alta Devices will use the
funds to improve the production of high efficiency solar
photovoltaic applications, it said. The company won U.S. Energy
Department funding of as much as $3 million in January to
develop its thin-film solar technology, according to the  agency .
The company also secured an undisclosed amount of funding in
November from GE.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ehren Goossens in  New York  at 
 egoossens1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
